        "schemeImageUrl": "",
        "detailedDescription_md": "The Post Matric and Top Class Scholarship under the Higher Education Department of the Madhya Pradesh government is to support students from economically disadvantaged backgrounds in pursuing higher education. Specifically, it aims to alleviate financial constraints by covering tuition fees, maintenance allowances, and other educational expenses. it aims to empower deserving students to excel academically and professionally, fostering their socio-economic development and contributing to the overall advancement of society.\n<br>\n\n",
        "benefits_md": "\n1. Hostel students receive a subsistence allowance of ₹1,200 per month.\n1. Non-hostel residents are provided with a subsistence allowance of ₹650 per month.\n\n> **Reimbursement of mandatory and non-refundable fees.**\n\n",
        "briefDescription": "The Scheme Post Matric and Top Class Scholarship for Madhya Pradesh is provide financial assistance to students from economically disadvantaged backgrounds to pursue higher education.",
